        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 3:58PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lithia, or near Montvale, moving north at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lexington...
Buchanan...
Glasgow...
Stewartsville...
Montvale...
Collierstown...
and Eagle Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
